{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἄστρον</b>, τό, <br /> mostly in <i>plural</i>, <b>the stars,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 8.555, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 12.312, 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 458, “Ag.” 4, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; τοῦ κατ᾽ ἄστρα Ζηνός, ={τοῦ ἐν οὐρανῷ}, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 1106\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἄστρων εὐφρόνη, ={εὐφρ. ἀστερόεσσα}, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “El.” 19: _sing._, like{ἀστήρ}, frequently of Sirius (in full, σήριον ἄστρον\">Refs</a>] probable reading in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 7th c.BC: Alcman Lyricus 23.63), 7th-6th c.BC: Alcaeus Lyricus 39, 40, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Cynegeticus” 4.6, 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “de Causis Plantarum” 6.10.9, +others\">Refs 7th c.BC+</a>]; περὶ τὸ ἄ. in the <b>dog-days,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “ἐπιδημίαι” 7.7\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <i>poetry</i> of the sun, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 1.6, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Definitiones” 411b\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: seldom of <b>any common star,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 17(1).16, Scholia 4th-3rd c.BC: Aratus Epicus 11 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; of the fixed stars, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “de Caelo” 290a20\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; ἄστρα πλανητά, opposed to ἀπλανῆ, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Timaeus” 38c\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; opposed to ἐνδεδεμένα, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Meteorologica” 346a2\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; opposed to ἀστέρες, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd-3rd c.AD: Hermes Trismegistus cited in 5th c.AD: Stobaeus, Joannes 1.21.9\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; ἐπὶ τοῖς ἄστροις at the times of <b>the stars'</b> rising or setting, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “Aër.” 10, 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Historia Animalium” 568a18\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἄστροις σημαίνεσθαι, τεκμαίρεσθαι, guide oneself by <b>the stars,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd-3rd c.AD: Aelianus “De Natura Animalium - Ar.Byzantine Epit.” 2.7, 7.48\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; ἄστροις τὸ λοιπὸν ἐκμετρούμενος χθόνα knowing its place only by <b>the stars,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 795: _metaphorically_, ἐχθροῖς ἄ. ὣς λάμψειν [prev. author] “El.” 66. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> of something <b>brilliant, admirable,</b> Ἀκροκόρινθον Ἑλλάδος ἄ.[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Anthologia Graeca” 7.297 (3rd c.BC: Polystratus Epicureus), compare 9.400 (6th c.AD: Palladas Epigrammaticus), “APl.” 4.295; Σωκρατικῆς σοφίης ἄ. “IG” 3.770 a.\">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G0798","accentedUnicode":"ἄστρον","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0792","matchingForm":"ἀστήρ","stepTransliteration":"astēr","gloss":"star","_zh_tw_Gloss":"星","_es_Gloss":"estrella","_zh_Gloss":"星"}],"shortDef":"star, constellation","mediumDef":"star, constellation <br /><b>a constellation; a star,</b> <ref='Luk.21.25'>Lk. 21:25</ref>; <ref='Act.7.43'>Acts 7:43;</ref> 27:20; <ref='Heb.11.12'>Heb. 11:12</ref>*","stepGloss":"star","stepTransliteration":"astron","count":4,"_es_Definition":"estrella, constelación","_zh_tw_Definition":"星星, 星座, 一顆星","_zh_Definition":"星星, 星座, 一颗星","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"ngôi sao","_zh_tw_Gloss":"星辰, 星","_es_Gloss":"estrella","_zh_Gloss":"星辰, 星"}]}